3.Missing data (impact on summaries): Which variables have the most missing values (e.g., delta_15n, delta_13c, sex, and the morphology measures), and how does missingness affect grouped summaries like mean(body_mass_g) by species when na.rm=FALSE vs na.rm=TRUE?
4.Duplicates (rows/IDs): Are there any fully duplicated rows in penguins_clean_names, and are there any duplicated individual_id values that indicate repeated measures (multiple records per penguin) rather than data entry duplicates?
5.Numeric plausibility (ranges/outliers): Are the ranges of numeric variables (body_mass_g, flipper_length_mm, culmen_length_mm, culmen_depth_mm, delta_15n, delta_13c) biologically plausible, and are there any impossible values (â‰¤0 for mass/length) or extreme outliers that need investigation?
